I really need to write better docs / example, but the short answer is that react-dimensions is a Higher-Order component that can be used like a mixin to add this.props.containerWidth and this.props.containerHeight to the component. Something like this:
``` js
import { Table } from 'fixed-data-table'
import GetContainerDimensions from 'react-dimensions'
class DataTable extends React.Component {
  render () {
    return (

        {columnNodes}

    )
  }
}
export default GetContainerDimensions()(DataTable)
```
