BracWebb:
Actually, using fixedDataTableRowLayout_rowWrapper is not ideal as you should use the public_ prefixed classnames. Also, as donnrri pointed out, this causes the header to highlight. These are the solutions you are looking for:
Hover and highlight header and body rows:
.public_fixedDataTableRow_main:hover .public_fixedDataTableCell_main {
  background-color: yellow;
}
Hover and highlight only the header:
.public_fixedDataTable_header:hover .public_fixedDataTableCell_main {
  background-color: yellow;
}
Hover and highlight only the body rows:
.public_fixedDataTable_bodyRow:hover .public_fixedDataTableCell_main {
  background-color: yellow;
}
Hover and highlight only the body rows, different for even and odd:
.public_fixedDataTableRow_even:hover .public_fixedDataTableCell_main {
  background-color: yellow;
}
.public_fixedDataTableRow_odd:hover .public_fixedDataTableCell_main {
  background-color: green;
